Bubbly and light. Unlike other minimally packaged sugar-free drinks like
[[Phocus|Phocus_Review]], this Tru actually tastes like something. The taste is
like sour apple gummies, like maybe those peach rings they sell at gas stations
but if they were sour apple. The bubbles make the drink crisp and smooth. It's
very enjoyable. Even though it lacks body because it's sugar-free this drink has
its place as a nice refresher on a hot day.

The interaction of l-theanine with caffeine supposedly helps taper the "jitters"
that caffeine gives you, hence why this blend is called "focus". In my
experience the effect is minimal in doses smaller than 200mg, which is about
where they max out for "nootropic" drinks like this. The label doesn't say how
much l-theanine so I can only guess it's less than 200mg based on what other
drinks contain. Finally, with just 100mg caffeine, there is not much energy to
taper.

